ZH: 脊骨是人体骨骼系统中最重要的一部分。
EN: The spine is the most important part of the human skeletal system.

ZH: 直立行走的灵长类动物都有脊骨的存在。
EN: The spine is present in all primates that walk upright.

ZH: 腰椎是脊骨中最容易受伤的部位之一。
EN: The lumbar vertebrae are one of the most prone areas of the spine to injury.

ZH: 脊骨的主要功能之一是支撑和保护脊髓。
EN: One of the main functions of the spine is to support and protect the spinal cord.

ZH: 脊骨的弯曲和扭转能够提供身体的灵活性。
EN: The curvature and twisting of the spine provide flexibility to the body.

ZH: 长期不良姿势会对脊骨造成伤害。
EN: Prolonged bad posture can cause damage to the spine.

ZH: 脊骨的变形可能导致严重的健康问题。
EN: Deformation of the spine can lead to serious health problems.

ZH: 错误的举重方式可能对脊骨造成损伤。
EN: Incorrect weightlifting techniques can cause damage to the spine.

ZH: 脊骨的强度和稳定性对保持身体平衡至关重要。
EN: The strength and stability of the spine are crucial for maintaining body balance.

ZH: 坐姿时，应该保持脊骨的自然曲线。
EN: When sitting, it is important to maintain the natural curvature of the spine.

ZH: 骨质疏松会增加脊骨骨折的风险。
EN: Osteoporosis increases the risk of spinal fractures.

ZH: 拥有良好的核心肌肉可以帮助保护脊骨。
EN: Having strong core muscles can help protect the spine.

ZH: 脊骨的神经压迫可能导致疼痛和麻木感。
EN: Nerve compression in the spine can cause pain and numbness.

ZH: 脊骨的问题可以通过物理治疗来改善。
EN: Issues with the spine can be improved through physical therapy.

ZH: 年龄增长会导致脊骨退行性变。
EN: Aging can result in degenerative changes in the spine.

ZH: 跳水运动员需要具备灵活且强壮的脊骨。
EN: Divers require a flexible and strong spine.

ZH: 扭伤脊骨可能需要一段时间的休息和康复。
EN: Twisting the spine may require a period of rest and rehabilitation.

ZH: 脊骨的损伤可能导致瘫痪。
EN: Injury to the spine can result in paralysis.

ZH: 每日锻炼可以帮助保持脊骨的健康。
EN: Regular exercise can help maintain the health of the spine.

ZH: 为了保护脊骨，应该避免重大冲击和跌倒。
EN: To protect the spine, it is advisable to avoid significant impacts and falls.
